STATE OF FLORIDA, ex rel. D. W. BRENNAN, as assignee of ALTON M. AKE, v. B. F. BUTLER, et al., (Broward County Port Authority). 13 So. (2nd) 2

January Term, 1943

April 6, 1943 En Banc Manley P. Caldwell, for appellant. T. O. Berry hill and C. L. Chancey, for appellees. PER CURIAM:

This is a companion case to State, ex rel. Drennan, as assignee of Alton M. Ake v. H. L. McCann, et ah, decided this date. The question raised is concluded by what we said in the last cited case so the judgment is reversed on authority thereof.

It is so ordered.

BUFORD, C. J., TERRELL, THOMAS and SEBRING, JJ., concur. BROWN, CHAPMAN and ADAMS, JJ., dissent.
